        boolean isValid(java.util.List<T> vector,
                int size)
        Checks if a vector prefix is valid. This method must check if the first @a size elements of @a vector are valid.
        Parameters:
        vector - The vector to check.
        size - The number of elements to check.
        Returns:
        true if the prefix is valid, false otherwise.
